cs.NI, cs.SI, cs.SY, cs.DS, cs.CE 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper discusses the impact of network structure on traffic dynamics and proposes link rewiring strategies to improve network transport efficiency. This falls under the scope of networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper discusses the structure of scale-free networks and how it affects network capacity. This falls under the scope of social and information networks. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes strategies to enhance network performance, which falls under the scope of systems and control. 
4. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper discusses the degree distribution of the network and how it remains the same after link rewiring. This falls under the scope of data structures and algorithms. 
5. cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) - The paper proposes strategies to improve network transport efficiency, which falls under the scope of computational engineering.
